The customer was using another platform and migrating to Shopify - planning to go live this month
&nbsp;
Customer expecting to process nearly 1000 orders per month, mostly using DHL Freight Sweden
In the customer use case return label is mandatory as they are selling high-value products
&nbsp;
Customers want to use PostNord only for low-value orders
&nbsp;
On call we discussed about account settings, rules update, and order processing, including generating labels, print document, fulfilling orders, pickup, ect
&nbsp;
At present customer using the 'wikinggruppen' platform to generate shipping labels - which provides DHL Freight Sweden Service Point Return as a service to generate return label and attached for your reference.
&nbsp;
However, in the app the DHL Freight Sweden return service is missing
&nbsp;
Customer mentioned that without return service they are not going to proceed with solusion - ChatGPT is saying DHL Freight Sweden does support return services
&nbsp;
Requested the customer to cross-check and confirm the account is enabled for return service
&nbsp;
Also customer reported the address layout on the label is not correct - the customer want below format
Company Name
Street
City ect
&nbsp;
But label generated in our app is printing
Street
Company
City ect
&nbsp;
Call recording video - https://drive.google.com/file/d/19USznWTBhpq2OP-C_hen6mTQMXn5H-Aq/view?usp=sharing
&nbsp;

Need Assistance from L3 Team
&nbsp;
Case: DHL Freight Sweden – Return Service Missing &amp; Address Format on DHL Labels
&nbsp;
Customer Plan: $29 Popular Plan (MCSL)
&nbsp;
Context: The customer raised the following two concerns during the onboarding call.
&nbsp;
 Case 1: DHL Freight Sweden – Service Point Return Option Missing The customer ships high-value products, and having a return option is mandatory for their business. They primarily use DHL Freight Sweden for their shipments and mentioned that they have been using DHL Freight Sweden for nearly 20 years.
&nbsp;
Currently, they are using the Wikinggruppen platform to generate labels and have confirmed that DHL Freight Sweden supports return services. However, they are unable to see the Service Point Return option in our app.
&nbsp;
 Case 2: Address Format on DHL Label Is Not as Expected The customer expects the address on the DHL label to be printed in the following format:
  Contact Person Name  Company Name  Street  City  Postcode  Country  However, labels generated via our app currently display the address as:
  Name  Street  Company  City  Postcode  Country  &nbsp;
The customer finds this format unusual and inconsistent with their existing DHL Freight Sweden labels. A sample return label shared by the customer has been attached for reference, and the address format can be cross-checked against it.
&nbsp;
Store Details:
  Store URL: jt4xkk-ub.myshopify.com   Account ID: d02d6df9-92e2-49d3-9962-b69e8ef72ec2   Plan: $29 Popular Plan  Order Volume: Up to 1000 orders per month (as informed by the customer)

